    "description": "<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Neon Colony</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Neon Colony is a tower defense game where you develop a reasonably uninhabited planet for your kind corporate benefactors. Plan your roads, extract the planet's resources and deal with any unruly and most definitively evil aliens in a diplomatic manner.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3192000/extras/14a8a3bc5e5639223d2e873d8c4f0d80.avif?t=1758738023\" width=400 height=107 /></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Game features</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Build your own road</strong>! Each new road tile can be rotated and replaced as you see fit to gain full control over the planet's surface - though replacing comes at a cost.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Discover</strong> more valuable <strong>resources</strong> further from your city, but also more dangerous enemies. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Use your resources to power advanced towers</strong> - unless you would rather <strong>sell</strong> <strong>them for intergalactic</strong> <strong>credits</strong>, which can be used to buy one of the <strong>100+ upgrades </strong>to your towers, city or economy.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Deal with</strong> <strong>alien ruins</strong> <strong>and artifacts </strong>that can drastically change the nature of a run.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Unlock and choose one of 15 governors</strong> to govern your colony, each with unique advantages and downsides.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>There is a challenge to each run</strong>, which can start with <strong>1-4 lanes</strong>, depending on your level of greed and with<strong> 15 levels </strong>determining how hospitable the planet is.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Easy to learn</strong>, with 5 optional tutorial levels that gradually introduce the game elements to you.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Play as you want</strong>! Finishing a run<strong> does not require meta-progression</strong>, with all essential upgrades available from the start.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Music by Karl Casey @ White Bat Audio </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Cover Art by Crumpaloo</p>",
